hh3cDot11CFG.description: This MIB provides information about WLAN configuration. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. Access point (AP) Transmitter/receiver (transceiver) device that commonly connects and transports data between a wireless network and a wired network. Access control (AC) To control and manage multi-APs, it will bridge wireless and wired network. Fat AP Applied in the home, SOHO and so on, and it could work independently without help from AC. Fit AP Applied in the enterprise environment, it will work under the control and management from AC. Control And Provisioning of Wireless Access Points Protocol The short name of protocol is CAPWAP. AC will control and manage AP by CAPWAP tunnel protocol defined by IETF. Also, a data tunnel will be set up between AC and AP. BSS IEEE 802.11 Basic Service Set (Radio Cell). The BSS of an AP comprises of the stations directly associating with the AP. Radio The chip set to receive and send wireless signal. Association The service used to establish access point or station mapping and enable station invocation of the distribution system services. (Wireless clients attempt to connect to access points.) Basic Rate A data rate that is mandatory for client devices to support in order for them to achieve successful association. MSDU MAC Service Data Unit, it is frame format defined by 802.11. TU It is 1,024 microseconds (ms), which is about 1 millisecond. AKM The authentication and key management method defined by 802.11i, and which includes 802.1x and pre-shared key.

hh3cDot11GlobalCountryCode.name: hh3cDot11GlobalCountryCode
hh3cDot11GlobalCountryCode.description: Represents the country code for wireless network.

hh3cDot11StaKeepALiveTimerIntvl.name: hh3cDot11StaKeepALiveTimerIntvl
hh3cDot11StaKeepALiveTimerIntvl.description: Represents the interval of the keep alive requests sent between AP and STA. Default value 0 : The keep alive function is disabled.

hh3cDot11StaIdleTimerIntvl.name: hh3cDot11StaIdleTimerIntvl
hh3cDot11StaIdleTimerIntvl.description: Represents the interval for which the link between AP and STA ( power-save or awake ) can be idle.

hh3cDot11BroadcastProbeReply.name: hh3cDot11BroadcastProbeReply
hh3cDot11BroadcastProbeReply.description: Represents enable the AP to reply broadcast probe or not. 'true' : The AP to reply broadcast probe is enabled. 'false': The AP to reply broadcast probe is disabled

hh3cDot11APScanMode.name: hh3cDot11APScanMode
hh3cDot11APScanMode.description: Represents the scanning mode for AP. The following values are supported: active - AP will actively do scan. passive - AP will passively do scan.

hh3cDot11ACCtrlTunnelSecSupport.name: hh3cDot11ACCtrlTunnelSecSupport
hh3cDot11ACCtrlTunnelSecSupport.description: Represents what security schemes are supported for CAPWAP Control tunnel.

hh3cDot11ACDataTunnelSecSupport.name: hh3cDot11ACDataTunnelSecSupport
hh3cDot11ACDataTunnelSecSupport.description: Represents what security schemes are supported for CAPWAP data tunnel. The cleartxt is the default scheme.

hh3cDot11ACAutoAPSupport.name: hh3cDot11ACAutoAPSupport
hh3cDot11ACAutoAPSupport.description: Represents enable the auto AP functionality or not. 'true' : The auto AP functionality is enabled. 'false': The auto AP functionality is disabled

hh3cDot11AutoAPName.name: hh3cDot11AutoAPName

hh3cDot11PersistentName.name: hh3cDot11PersistentName

hh3cDot11IntfTrapThreshold.name: hh3cDot11IntfTrapThreshold
hh3cDot11IntfTrapThreshold.description: Represents threshold of interference trap. If signal strength of the device exceeds this threshold, corresponding trap will be sent.

hh3cDot11MonitorInterval.name: hh3cDot11MonitorInterval
hh3cDot11MonitorInterval.description: Represents the monitoring interval. Default value 0 : The monitoring functionality is changed to real-time mode.

hh3cDot11SampleInterval.name: hh3cDot11SampleInterval
hh3cDot11SampleInterval.description: Represents the sampling interval. Default value 0 : The sampling functionality is disabled.

hh3cDot11ChnlSwitChkInterval.name: hh3cDot11ChnlSwitChkInterval
hh3cDot11ChnlSwitChkInterval.description: Represents the checking interval of channel switch.

hh3cDot11APUserUplimit.name: hh3cDot11APUserUplimit
hh3cDot11APUserUplimit.description: Represents the upper limit of user which has access to this AP.

hh3cDot11APL2IsolateEnable.name: hh3cDot11APL2IsolateEnable
hh3cDot11APL2IsolateEnable.description: Represents enable the layer2 isolation or not. 'true' : The layer2 isolation functionality is enabled. 'false': The layer2 isolation functionality is disabled.

hh3cDot11APBSSIDSupportNum.name: hh3cDot11APBSSIDSupportNum
hh3cDot11APBSSIDSupportNum.description: Represents the max number of BSSID supported by Current AP.

hh3cDot11APLastUpdateStatTime.name: hh3cDot11APLastUpdateStatTime
hh3cDot11APLastUpdateStatTime.description: Represents date and time update statistic information lately.

hh3cDot11APDoSProtectEnable.name: hh3cDot11APDoSProtectEnable
hh3cDot11APDoSProtectEnable.description: Represents enable the DOS protection or not. 'true' : The DOS protection functionality is enabled. 'false': The DOS protection functionality is disabled.

hh3cDot11MaxAPPerIf.name: hh3cDot11MaxAPPerIf
hh3cDot11MaxAPPerIf.description: Represents max AP number that can be connected to AC interface.

hh3cDot11SampleTimeStamp.name: hh3cDot11SampleTimeStamp
hh3cDot11SampleTimeStamp.description: Represents the start time of current sample period.

hh3cDot11UplinkTrackId.name: hh3cDot11UplinkTrackId
hh3cDot11UplinkTrackId.description: Represents the track id of AP. Default value 0 : The uplink track function for AP is disabled.

hh3cDot11RtCollectSwitch.name: hh3cDot11RtCollectSwitch
hh3cDot11RtCollectSwitch.description: This object is used to turn on/off real-time statistics collection between AC and AP. If the value is true, hh3cDot11RtCollectIntvl will take effect. Otherwise, hh3cDot11RglCollectIntvl will take effect.

hh3cDot11RglCollectIntvl.name: hh3cDot11RglCollectIntvl
hh3cDot11RglCollectIntvl.description: This object represents interval to regularly collect statistics from AC to AP.

hh3cDot11RtCollectIntvl.name: hh3cDot11RtCollectIntvl
hh3cDot11RtCollectIntvl.description: This object represents interval to collect real-time statistics from AC to AP.

hh3cDot11AllAPCpuUsageThreshold.name: hh3cDot11AllAPCpuUsageThreshold
hh3cDot11AllAPCpuUsageThreshold.description: The CPU usage threshold for all AP.

hh3cDot11AllAPMemUsageThreshold.name: hh3cDot11AllAPMemUsageThreshold
hh3cDot11AllAPMemUsageThreshold.description: The memory usage threshold for all AP.

hh3cDot11AdjIntfTrapThreshold.name: hh3cDot11AdjIntfTrapThreshold
hh3cDot11AdjIntfTrapThreshold.description: Represents threshold of adjacent interference trap. If signal strength of the device exceeds this threshold, corresponding trap will be sent.

hh3cDot11AllAPMonitorMode.name: hh3cDot11AllAPMonitorMode
hh3cDot11AllAPMonitorMode.description: Represents what work mode for All AP. The following values are supported: normal, - AP will supply WLAN service. monitor - AP will be a monitor to find attack. hybrid - AP will supply WLAN service and Device detection is enabled.

hh3cDot11GlobalApFmwUpdState.name: hh3cDot11GlobalApFmwUpdState
hh3cDot11GlobalApFmwUpdState.description: Represents the status of version auto-update for an AP. The following values are supported: enable - AP version will be updated automatically. disable - AP version will not be updated automatically.

hh3cDot11ACNasIDCM.name: hh3cDot11ACNasIDCM
hh3cDot11ACNasIDCM.description: Represents the NAS-ID of current AC.

hh3cDot11RadioPolicyTable.name: hh3cDot11RadioPolicyTable
hh3cDot11RadioPolicyTable.description: The table defines the parameters for radio policy, as per radio policy of CLI. One radio policy could be assigned to the different radios (AP).

hh3cDot11RadioPolicyEntry.name: hh3cDot11RadioPolicyEntry
hh3cDot11RadioPolicyEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each radio policy.

hh3cDot11RadioPolicyName.name: hh3cDot11RadioPolicyName
hh3cDot11RadioPolicyName.description: Represents the name of radio policy.

hh3cDot11BeaconInterval.name: hh3cDot11BeaconInterval
hh3cDot11BeaconInterval.description: Represents the interval for Beacon management frame.

hh3cDot11DtimInterval.name: hh3cDot11DtimInterval
hh3cDot11DtimInterval.description: Represents the number of beacon intervals that shall elapse between transmission of Beacons frames containing a Traffic Indication Map (TIM) element whose DTIM Count field is 0. This value is transmitted in the Delivery TIM (DTIM) Period field of Beacon frames.

hh3cDot11RtsThreshold.name: hh3cDot11RtsThreshold
hh3cDot11RtsThreshold.description: Represents the current minimum size, in octets, of the MAC protocol data unit (MPDU), below which a Request to send/Clear to send (RTS/CTS) handshake shall not be performed.

hh3cDot11FragThreshold.name: hh3cDot11FragThreshold
hh3cDot11FragThreshold.description: Represents the current maximum size, in octets, of the MPDU that may be delivered to the PHY. A MSDU shall be broken into fragments if its size exceeds the value of this attribute after adding MAC headers and trailers.

hh3cDot11ShortRetryThreshold.name: hh3cDot11ShortRetryThreshold
hh3cDot11ShortRetryThreshold.description: Represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is less than or equal to hh3cDot11RTSThreshold, which shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

hh3cDot11LongRetryThreshold.name: hh3cDot11LongRetryThreshold
hh3cDot11LongRetryThreshold.description: Represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is longer than hh3cDot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

hh3cDot11MaxRxLifetime.name: hh3cDot11MaxRxLifetime
hh3cDot11MaxRxLifetime.description: Represents the elapsed time. After the time specified by hh3cDot11MaxRxLifetime, the further attempts to reassemble the MSDU shall be terminated.

hh3cDot11RdoPolicyRowStatus.name: hh3cDot11RdoPolicyRowStatus
hh3cDot11RdoPolicyRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cDot11RdoClientMaxCount.name: hh3cDot11RdoClientMaxCount
hh3cDot11RdoClientMaxCount.description: Represent the maximum number of stations supported by this radio policy.

hh3cDot11BeaconIntervalMs.name: hh3cDot11BeaconIntervalMs
hh3cDot11BeaconIntervalMs.description: Represents the interval for Beacon management frame.

hh3cDot11ServicePolicyTable.name: hh3cDot11ServicePolicyTable
hh3cDot11ServicePolicyTable.description: The table defines the parameters for ESS, as per service policy of CLI. One service policy could be assigned to the different radios (AP).

hh3cDot11ServicePolicyEntry.name: hh3cDot11ServicePolicyEntry
hh3cDot11ServicePolicyEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each service policy.

hh3cDot11ServicePolicyID.name: hh3cDot11ServicePolicyID
hh3cDot11ServicePolicyID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

hh3cDot11SSIDName.name: hh3cDot11SSIDName
hh3cDot11SSIDName.description: Represents the ESS. As per CLI, the value of service policy name will be SSID.

hh3cDot11SSIDHidden.name: hh3cDot11SSIDHidden
hh3cDot11SSIDHidden.description: This attribute controls whether the SSID will be advertised in the beacon frame. If it is true, then SSID will not be advertised in the beacon frame.

hh3cDot11AuthenMode.name: hh3cDot11AuthenMode
hh3cDot11AuthenMode.description: Represents the Authentication mode defined by 802.11.

hh3cDot11SSIDEncryptionMode.name: hh3cDot11SSIDEncryptionMode
hh3cDot11SSIDEncryptionMode.description: Represents the encryption mode for this ESS.

hh3cDot11WlanInfBindingType.name: hh3cDot11WlanInfBindingType
hh3cDot11WlanInfBindingType.description: Represents the service policy will bind to what kind of data forwarding interface.

hh3cDot11WlanInfBindingID.name: hh3cDot11WlanInfBindingID
hh3cDot11WlanInfBindingID.description: Represents the interface ID of the interface that ESS will bind to. If the value is set to -1, the binding will be removed.

hh3cDot11SrvPolicyRowStatus.name: hh3cDot11SrvPolicyRowStatus
hh3cDot11SrvPolicyRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cDot11ClientMaxCount.name: hh3cDot11ClientMaxCount
hh3cDot11ClientMaxCount.description: Represent the maximum number of stations supported by this service policy.

hh3cDot11SPInCirMode.name: hh3cDot11SPInCirMode
hh3cDot11SPInCirMode.description: CIR(committed information rate) mode of inbound direction. This object is useful only when the corresponding CIR is nonzero. If value of this object is changed, corresponding CIR will be reset.

hh3cDot11SPInCirValue.name: hh3cDot11SPInCirValue
hh3cDot11SPInCirValue.description: Represents the CIR of inbound direction of this service policy. If the value is 0, it means that no flow control is applied to the service policy, and the corresponding CIR mode is meaningless.

hh3cDot11SPOutCirMode.name: hh3cDot11SPOutCirMode
hh3cDot11SPOutCirMode.description: CIR(committed information rate) mode of outbound direction. This object is useful only when the corresponding CIR is nonzero. If value of this object is changed, corresponding CIR will be reset.

hh3cDot11SPOutCirValue.name: hh3cDot11SPOutCirValue
hh3cDot11SPOutCirValue.description: Represents the CIR of outbound direction of this service policy. If the value is 0, it means that no flow control is applied to the service policy, and the corresponding CIR mode is meaningless.

hh3cDot11WlanInfPVID.name: hh3cDot11WlanInfPVID
hh3cDot11WlanInfPVID.description: Represents the VLAN ID of SSID.

hh3cDot11SPInCirStaticValue.name: hh3cDot11SPInCirStaticValue
hh3cDot11SPInCirStaticValue.description: Represents the CIR of inbound direction for static CIR mode.

hh3cDot11SPOutCirStaticValue.name: hh3cDot11SPOutCirStaticValue
hh3cDot11SPOutCirStaticValue.description: Represents the CIR of outbound direction for static CIR mode.

hh3cDot11SPIsolate.name: hh3cDot11SPIsolate
hh3cDot11SPIsolate.description: If it is true, then stations connected with the service policy are isolated.

hh3cDot11WlanexAuthServerIP.name: hh3cDot11WlanexAuthServerIP
hh3cDot11WlanexAuthServerIP.description: Represents the IP address of the Wlanex Authentication server

hh3cDot11SPBeaconMeasEnable.name: hh3cDot11SPBeaconMeasEnable
hh3cDot11SPBeaconMeasEnable.description: If it is true, then beacon-measurement is enabled.

hh3cDot11SPBeaconMeasType.name: hh3cDot11SPBeaconMeasType
hh3cDot11SPBeaconMeasType.description: Represents what the work mode for BeaconMeasurement type. The following values are supported: passive, - BeaconMeasurement will use the passive type. active - BeaconMeasurement will use the active type. beaconTable - BeaconMeasurement will use the beacon table type.

hh3cDot11AuthenModeCM.name: hh3cDot11AuthenModeCM
hh3cDot11AuthenModeCM.description: Represents the Authentication mode defined by 802.11.

hh3cDot11SecIEStatusCM.name: hh3cDot11SecIEStatusCM
hh3cDot11SecIEStatusCM.description: To enable the security Information element in the beacon and probe response frames sent by AP.

hh3cDot11SecurityCiphersCM.name: hh3cDot11SecurityCiphersCM
hh3cDot11SecurityCiphersCM.description: The WLAN system support the following cipher type for data frame encryption. none wep40 wep104 tkip aesccmp wpi-SMS4 When the value of node equals to zero, it means no configuration or undo operation.

hh3cDot11SrvPolicyStatusCM.name: hh3cDot11SrvPolicyStatusCM
hh3cDot11SrvPolicyStatusCM.description: The status of the Service Policy.

hh3cDot11SSIDHiddenCM.name: hh3cDot11SSIDHiddenCM
hh3cDot11SSIDHiddenCM.description: This attribute controls whether the SSID will be advertised in beacon frames. If it is dot11true, the SSID will not be advertised in beacon frames.

hh3cDot11SPIsolateCM.name: hh3cDot11SPIsolateCM
hh3cDot11SPIsolateCM.description: If it is dot11true, the clients connected with the service policy are isolated to each other.

hh3cDot11ServicePolicyExtTable.name: hh3cDot11ServicePolicyExtTable
hh3cDot11ServicePolicyExtTable.description: The table defines the parameters for ESS, as per service policy of CLI. When the value of hh3cDot11SSIDEncryptionMode equals to cipher(2), more configuration for a ESS will be put into the table.

hh3cDot11ServicePolicyExtEntry.name: hh3cDot11ServicePolicyExtEntry
hh3cDot11ServicePolicyExtEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each service policy under cipher(2) mode.

hh3cDot11ServicePolicyExtID.name: hh3cDot11ServicePolicyExtID
hh3cDot11ServicePolicyExtID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

hh3cDot11SecIEStatus.name: hh3cDot11SecIEStatus
hh3cDot11SecIEStatus.description: To enable the security Information element in the beacon and probe response frames sent by AP.

hh3cDot11SecurityCiphers.name: hh3cDot11SecurityCiphers
hh3cDot11SecurityCiphers.description: The WLAN system support the following cipher type for data frame encryption. wep40(2) tkip(4) aesccmp(16) wep104(32) wpisms4(64) wep128(128) For each service policy, it could support multiple cipher types at the same time. So the value of object could combine multiple value of cipher type above. When the value of node equals to zero, it means no configuration or undo operation.

hh3cDot11CipherKeyIndex.name: hh3cDot11CipherKeyIndex
hh3cDot11CipherKeyIndex.description: Represents the key index of cipher key for packet. When hh3cDot11SecurityCiphers value is wep40 or wep104, the configuration will take effective.

hh3cDot11CipherKey.name: hh3cDot11CipherKey
hh3cDot11CipherKey.description: Represents the cipher key for packet. When hh3cDot11SecurityCiphers value is wep40 or wep104, the configuration will take effective.

hh3cDot11SrvPolicyExtRowStatus.name: hh3cDot11SrvPolicyExtRowStatus
hh3cDot11SrvPolicyExtRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cDot11CipherKeyType.name: hh3cDot11CipherKeyType
hh3cDot11CipherKeyType.description: Represents the cipher key type of hh3cDot11CipherKey.

hh3cDot11RadioPolicyExtTable.name: hh3cDot11RadioPolicyExtTable
hh3cDot11RadioPolicyExtTable.description: The table defines the radio policy of each radio. It can't be modified if the radio policy is a default radio policy.

hh3cDot11RadioPolicyExtEntry.name: hh3cDot11RadioPolicyExtEntry
hh3cDot11RadioPolicyExtEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each radio policy.

hh3cDot11RPAPSerialID.name: hh3cDot11RPAPSerialID
hh3cDot11RPAPSerialID.description: This object represents the Serial ID of AP.

hh3cDot11RPBeaconInterval.name: hh3cDot11RPBeaconInterval
hh3cDot11RPBeaconInterval.description: This object represents the interval for Beacon management frame.

hh3cDot11RPDtimInterval.name: hh3cDot11RPDtimInterval
hh3cDot11RPDtimInterval.description: This object represents the number of beacon intervals that shall elapse between transmissions of Beacons frames containing a Traffic Indication Map (TIM) element whose DTIM count field is 0. This value is transmitted in the Delivery TIM (DTIM) Period field of Beacon frames.

hh3cDot11RPRtsThreshold.name: hh3cDot11RPRtsThreshold
hh3cDot11RPRtsThreshold.description: This object represents the current minimum size, in octets, of the MAC protocol data unit (MPDU), below which a Request to send/Clear to send (RTS/CTS) handshake shall not be performed.

hh3cDot11RPFragThreshold.name: hh3cDot11RPFragThreshold
hh3cDot11RPFragThreshold.description: This object represents the current maximum size, in octets, of the MPDU that may be delivered to the PHY. A MSDU shall be broken into fragments if its size exceeds the value of this attribute after adding MAC headers and trailers.

hh3cDot11RPShortRetryThreshold.name: hh3cDot11RPShortRetryThreshold
hh3cDot11RPShortRetryThreshold.description: This object represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is less than or equal to hh3cDot11RTSThreshold, that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

hh3cDot11RPLongRetryThreshold.name: hh3cDot11RPLongRetryThreshold
hh3cDot11RPLongRetryThreshold.description: This object represents the maximum number of transmission attempts of a frame, the length of which is longer than hh3cDot11RTSThreshold, and that shall be made before a failure condition is indicated.

hh3cDot11RPClientMaxCount.name: hh3cDot11RPClientMaxCount
hh3cDot11RPClientMaxCount.description: This object represents the maximum number of stations supported by this radio policy.

hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityTable.name: hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityTable
hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityTable.description: This table defines the WLAN security status for ESS, BSS and WLAN-Ethernet interface which binding the crypto service-template. Otherwise, when binding the clear service-template, hh3cPortSecurityTables should be used to configure port security.

hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityEntry.name: hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityEntry
hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityEntry.description: There is a row in this table for service policy.

hh3cDot11SecurityServicePolicyID.name: hh3cDot11SecurityServicePolicyID
hh3cDot11SecurityServicePolicyID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityMode.name: hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityMode
hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityMode.description: Determines the security modes of the WLAN port. noRestrictions The default value, no any security mode is set. userLoginSecureExt Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X). psk Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X key negotiation). macAddressAndPsk The MAC address is first authenticated and only if this succeeds does the psk then attempt user authentication. userLoginSecureExtOrPsk This selects both the userLoginSecureExt and psk modes together such that either is allowed to authorized access. Which mode works for client depends on the client's choice. ext Access to the port is denied until the port client is authenticated (by ext).

hh3cDot11SrvSecurityKeyType.name: hh3cDot11SrvSecurityKeyType
hh3cDot11SrvSecurityKeyType.description: This indicates the key type in the 802.1X EAPOL_Key packet. userLoginTxKeyTypeNone - This means the key type is not set yet. userLoginTxKeyTypeDot11Key - This selects the 802.11 key type. userLoginTxKeyTypeRsaRC4Key - This selects the RC4 key for RSA RC4 session encryption.

hh3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyMode.name: hh3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyMode
hh3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyMode.description: This is the password input mode. When input as pskKeyModePassPhrase, hh3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString must be 8 to 63 characters; when input as pskKeyModeRawKey, hh3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString must be 64 characters and each character must be '0'-'9', 'a'-'f' and 'A'-'F'.

hh3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString.name: hh3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString
hh3cDot11SrvSecurityPskKeyString.description: This is the password string used for psk authentication.

hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityModeCM.name: hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityModeCM
hh3cDot11SrvPortSecurityModeCM.description: Determines the security modes of the WLAN port. none - The default value, no any security mode is set. psk - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X key negotiation). radius - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X). wlanex - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authenticated by wlan cert.

hh3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendTable.name: hh3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendTable
hh3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendTable.description: The table defines the parameters of each service policy.

hh3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendEntry.name: hh3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendEntry
hh3cDot11SrvPolicyExtendEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each service policy.

hh3cDot11SPEnable.name: hh3cDot11SPEnable
hh3cDot11SPEnable.description: Represents whether the service policy is enabled.

hh3cDot11APTemplateTable.name: hh3cDot11APTemplateTable
hh3cDot11APTemplateTable.description: By AP template CLI, administrator will configure the parameters of AP by convenience. Before AP boot up and connect to AC by CAPWAP tunnel, administrator will create AP template for each AP. When AP connect to AC, AC will assign configuration to AP by hh3cDot11APSerialID information in AP template.

hh3cDot11APTemplateEntry.name: hh3cDot11APTemplateEntry
hh3cDot11APTemplateEntry.description: Each entry contains configuration information for each AP.

hh3cDot11APTemplateName.name: hh3cDot11APTemplateName
hh3cDot11APTemplateName.description: Represents the name of AP template.

hh3cDot11TemplateAPModelAlias.name: hh3cDot11TemplateAPModelAlias
hh3cDot11TemplateAPModelAlias.description: Represents the alias of AP model name.

hh3cDot11Description.name: hh3cDot11Description
hh3cDot11Description.description: This attribute will give more information about AP. Administrator could suggest the location, owner or other information for each AP. If the value is set to NULL, the description will be removed.

hh3cDot11APWorkMode.name: hh3cDot11APWorkMode
hh3cDot11APWorkMode.description: Represents what work mode for AP. The following values are supported: normal - AP will supply WLAN service. monitor - AP will be a monitor to find attack. hybrid - AP will supply WLAN service and Device detection is enabled.

hh3cDot11APTemplateRowStatus.name: hh3cDot11APTemplateRowStatus
hh3cDot11APTemplateRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cDot11StatisInterv.name: hh3cDot11StatisInterv
hh3cDot11StatisInterv.description: Represents the interval of radio statistic.

hh3cDot11APBroadcastProbeReply.name: hh3cDot11APBroadcastProbeReply
hh3cDot11APBroadcastProbeReply.description: Represents enable the AP to reply broadcast probe or not. 'true' : The AP to reply broadcast probe is enabled. 'false': The AP to reply broadcast probe is disabled

hh3cDot11StaIdleTimerInterv.name: hh3cDot11StaIdleTimerInterv
hh3cDot11StaIdleTimerInterv.description: Represents the interval for which the link between AP and STA ( power-save or awake ) can be idle.

hh3cDot11StaKeepAliveTimerInterv.name: hh3cDot11StaKeepAliveTimerInterv
hh3cDot11StaKeepAliveTimerInterv.description: Represents the interval of the keep alive requests sent between AP and STA.

hh3cDot11APCir.name: hh3cDot11APCir
hh3cDot11APCir.description: Represents the committed information rate between AP and AC.

hh3cDot11APCbs.name: hh3cDot11APCbs
hh3cDot11APCbs.description: Represents the committed burst size between AP and AC.

hh3cDot11APPriorityLevel.name: hh3cDot11APPriorityLevel
hh3cDot11APPriorityLevel.description: This object represents the connection priority for the AP. If the connection priority is 7, the AC is considered as the primary AC for the AP.

hh3cDot11RCRadioRate.description: Set data transmit rates for the radio, in the format of 1,2,5.5... For 802.11n radios, the format can be MCS X. The data transmit rates between AP and STA must fall into the configured rates. (Note: For 802.11n radios, the first value will be treated as a mandatory rate, and the second value will be treated as a supported rate. If you configure more than two rates, the configuration cannot take effect. If you configure only one rate, it is considered as the mandatory rate by default.)

hh3cDot11RCRadioType2.description: This object represents the radio will work with which 802.11 radio type.

hh3cDot11RCPreambleLenCM.description: This object represents whether use long or short preamble for 802.11 MAC frame. When hh3cDot11CfgRadioType is either dot11b or dot11g, then value for hh3cDot11PreambleLenCM will be valid. Otherwise, the value for it will be invalid.

The data transmit rates between AP and client should be one of the configured rates. (Note: For 802.11n radios, the first value is mandatory rate, and the second value is supported rate. If more than two rate values are configured, the configuration will not take effect. If only one rate value is configured, the mandatory rate will be set to the default value.)

hh3cDot11RadioCfgRtsThreshold.name: hh3cDot11RadioCfgRtsThreshold

hh3cDot11RadioCfgMaxRxLifetime.name: hh3cDot11RadioCfgMaxRxLifetime

hh3cDot11PortSecurityMode.name: hh3cDot11PortSecurityMode
hh3cDot11PortSecurityMode.description: Determines the security modes of the WLAN port. noRestrictions - The default value,no any security mode is set. userLoginSecureExt - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X). psk - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authorized (by 802.1X key negotiation). macAddressAndPsk - The MAC address is first authenticated and only if this succeeds does the psk then attempt user authentication. userLoginSecureExtOrPsk - This selects both the userLoginSecureExt and psk modes together such that either is allowed to authorized access. Which mode works for client depends on the client's choice. ext - Access to the port is denied until the port client is authenticated (by ext).

hh3cDot11SecurityUserLoginTxKeyType.name: hh3cDot11SecurityUserLoginTxKeyType
hh3cDot11SecurityUserLoginTxKeyType.description: This indicates the key type in the 802.1X EAPOL_Key packet. userLoginTxKeyTypeNone - This means the key type is not set yet. userLoginTxKeyTypeDot11Key - This selects the 802.11 key type. userLoginTxKeyTypeRsaRC4Key - This selects the RC4 key for RSA RC4 session encryption.

hh3cDot11SecurityPskKeyMode.name: hh3cDot11SecurityPskKeyMode
hh3cDot11SecurityPskKeyMode.description: This is the password input mode. When input as pskKeyModePassPhrase, hh3cDot11SecurePskKeyString must be 8 to 63 characters; when input as pskKeyModeRawKey, hh3cDot11SecurePskKeyString must be 64 characters and each character must be '0'-'9', 'a'-'f' and 'A'-'F'.

hh3cDot11SecurityPskKeyString.name: hh3cDot11SecurityPskKeyString
